data.reasoningText:
Let me plan the component decomposition for this settings dashboard, then implement it.

## Component Plan: Settings Dashboard

### Component Tree
```
Settings                    (page — orchestrates sections, owns active tab)
├── SettingsSidebar          (vertical tab nav)
├── ProfileSection           (profile editing)
├── NotificationsSection     (notification preferences)
├── SecuritySection          (password, 2FA, sessions)
│   ├── ChangePasswordPanel  (expandable password form)
│   └── SessionRevokeDialog  (confirmation dialog)
└── AppearanceSection        (theme, font, language, preview)


```

Now I'm mapping out the data flow — the Settings page will manage the active section and all settings state, passing data down to each section through parameters and handling updates through callbacks. I'll start by building the service interface and models, then work through the components from the bottom up before tying everything together in the main Settings page.

The namespace is `sv_265be80becbf417bb05a68211a3d0836`, and I'm organizing the files into a Services folder for the interface and models, with all the Settings components living in `Components/Pages/Settings/`. I'll create the service interface first, then build out each component with its corresponding CSS isolation file.

```

csharp
// Services/ISettingsService.cs
public interface ISettingsService
{
    Task<UserSettings> GetSettingsAsync();
    Task UpdateProfileAsync(ProfileUpdate update);
    Task UpdateNotificationsAsync(NotificationSettings settings);
    Task ChangePasswordAsync(PasswordChange change);
    Task RevokeSessionAsync(string sessionId);
    Task UpdateAppearanceAsync(AppearanceSettings settings);
}

public class UserSettings
{
    public string UserId { get; set; }
    public ProfileData Profile { get; set; }
    public NotificationSettings Notifications { get; set; }
    public AppearanceSettings Appearance { get; set; }
    public List<SessionInfo> ActiveSessions { get; set; }
}

public class ProfileData
{
    public string DisplayName { get; set; }
    public string Email { get; set; }
    public string Avatar { get; set; }
    public string Bio { get; set; }
}

public class NotificationSettings
{
    public bool EmailNotifications { get; set; }
    public bool PushNotifications { get; set; }
    public bool WeeklyDigest { get; set; }
}

public class AppearanceSettings
{
    public string Theme { get; set; }
    public string FontSize { get; set; }
    public bool HighContrast { get; set; }
}

public class SessionInfo
{
    public string SessionId { get; set; }
    public string DeviceName { get; set; }
    public DateTime LastActive { get; set; }
    public bool IsCurrent { get; set; }
}
```

Now I'll create the sidebar component that handles navigation between sections.

```razor
